>         How can you run an Amd DX4-120 chip in a PCI motherboard when the
> pci bus is only rated at 33Mhz?  I thought the 120 clock tripled a 40 Mhz
> bus speed.  Does this mean a 120Mhz chip in a pci mb will run at
> 100Mhz(3X33)?  I suppose if this were the case, if I wanted pci I should
> get the Amd5x86-133(4X33).  All comments appreciated.
> --
>                                              chrisch@netcom.com

Ummmm.... where is it written that the PCI bus and the CPU must
share common oscillators ????

It is quite possible to design a motherboard with independent clock
frequencies (sp) for the I/O Bus (PCI) and CPU.  I cannot answer
for the particular motherboard, but it is being done.  Some 75 MHz
Pentiums currently run two oscillators, one for the PCI bus and one
for the CPU bus.

