  I've been wondering about this question myself.  As I understand it, the PCI
bus speed does not have to be synchronous with the microprocessor bus speed.
You could have a separate 33MHz oscillator running the PCI bus, while the
processor bus is at 40MHz.  Or maybe run the 40MHz clock thru a 5:6 PLL to get
33MHz, or 3:4 to get 30MHz.  I don't know if any motherboards actually do this
or not, all of the Pentium Triton-based boards I've heard about just divide the
processor bus speed by 2 to get the PCI bus speed.  If they do that on dx4-120
and 5x86-120 boards, there's no way I'd buy one.  Running a PCI bus at 20MHz is
a complete waste.  Does anyone out there own a m/b like this?  Does the manual
shed any enlightenment on the actual PCI bus speed?

  Dave

